=MID(CELL("filename"),SEARCH("[",CELL("filename"))+1,SEARCH("]",CELL("filename"))-SEARCH("[",CELL("filename"))-1)

To add a named range in Excel 2010, click on the Formulas ribbon and under the Defined Names group, select Define Name. This will open the New Name dialog box. Enter, FileName, in the Name box; enter =GET.CELL(66) in the Refers to box; and click OK. Finally, enter, =FileName, into a cell to return the file name of the active workbook.

